Gore was endorsed by Hillary Clinton, Rep. Patrick Kennedy, 600 Latino leaders and California's Governor, two Senators and most if its Democratic congress people.
Tipper Gore spoke at the first Gay-Lesbian fundraiser for Gore in Washington in July 1999 and more women were hired for the campaign staff: Press Secretary, deputy Campaign Chair and pollster.
Tony Coelho was appointed General Chairman that summer and it was noted that the center of gravity had shifted from the Vice Presidential office to the campaign.
In September planned movement of the campaign headquarters from Washington to Nashville was announced.
